Netflix's average monthly revenue per paying membership (ARM) increased from $10.82 in fiscal year 2019 to $11.70 in fiscal year 2024, a nominal increase of $0.88 (8.1%). However, the 2024 figure is not directly comparable to 2019 because starting in 2024, Netflix excludes extra member sub accounts from the paid membership count but still includes their revenue in the ARM calculation; no such exclusion existed in 2019. Therefore, the underlying like-for-like increase in average revenue per core paying member is smaller than the reported 8.1% change, though the exact magnitude of this effect is not separately quantified in the available filings.

