TJX beat its Q4 FY2025 pre-tax margin guidance by 70 basis points (actual 11.6% vs the high-end of guidance 10.9%).

**Calculation:**  
Actual pre-tax margin = 11.6%  
High-end guidance = 10.9%  
Difference = 11.6% - 10.9% = 0.7 percentage points = 70 bps.

**Evidence:**  
TJX's Q4 FY2025 earnings release (8-K filed Feb 26, 2025) reports a pretax profit margin of 11.6% and states it was "above the high-end of its plan by 0.7 percentage points" (i.e., 70 bps). Guidance from the prior quarter's release was 10.8%–10.9%.

